accession": "PRIDE:0000404", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/14_4_16_2_Rwt_410b_72h.raw"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000404", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/14_4_16_3_Rwt_410c_72h.raw"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000404", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/14_4_16_6_Rwt_480c_72h_160418162605.raw"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000408", "name": "Search engine output file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/txt1.zip"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000404", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/14_4_16_4_Rwt_480a_72h.raw"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000404", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/14_4_16_5_Rwt_480b_72h.raw"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000403", "name": "Associated file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443/Yeast_Aug2015.fasta"}], "description": "Cellular redox status affects diverse cellular functions, including proliferation, protein homeostasis, and aging. Thus, individual differences in redox status can give rise to distinct sub-populations even among cells with identical genetic backgrounds. Here, we have created a novel methodology to track redox status at single cell resolution using the redox-sensitive probe roGFP. Our method allows identification and sorting of sub-populations with different oxidation levels in either the cytosol, mitochondria or peroxisomes. Using this approach we defined redox-dependent heterogeneity of yeast cells, and characterized growth, as well as proteomic and transcriptomic profiles of subpopulations of cells that differ in their redox status, but are similar in age. We report that, starting in late logarithmic growth, cells of the same age have a bi-modal distribution of oxidation status. A comparative proteomic analysis between these populations identified three key proteins, Hsp30, Dhh1, and Pnc1, which affect basal oxidation levels and may serve as first line of defense proteins in redox homeostasis.", "fullDatasetLinks": [{"accession": "PRIDE:0000411", "name": "Dataset FTP location", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2018/06/PXD009443"}, {"accession": "MS:1001930", "name": "PRIDE project URI", "value": "http://www.ebi.ac.uk/pride/archive/projects/PXD009443"}], "identifiers": [{"accession": "MS:1001919", "name": "ProteomeXchange accession number", "value": "PXD009443"}], "instruments": [{"accession": "MS:1001911", "name": "Q Exactive"}], "keywords": [{"accession": "MS:1001925", "name": "submitter keyword", "value": "redox, yeast"}, {"accession": "MS:1001926", "name": "curator keyword", "value": "Biological"}], "modifications": [{"accession": "MOD:00425", "name": "monohydroxylated residue"}, {"accession": "MOD:00399", "name": "iodoacetic acid derivatized residue"}], "publications": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1000879", "name": "PubMed identifier", "value": "29869985"}, {"accession": "PRIDE:0000400", "name": "Reference", "value": "Radzinski M, Fassler R, Yogev O, Breuer W, Shai N, Gutin J, Ilyas S, Geffen Y, Tsytkin-Kirschenzweig S, Nahmias Y, Ravid T, Friedman N, Shuldiner M, Reichmann D. Temporal profiling of redox-dependent heterogeneity in single cells. Elife. 2018 7"}]}], "species": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1001469", "name": "taxonomy: scientific name", "value": "Saccharomyces cerevisiae (Baker's yeast)"}, {"accession": "MS:1001467", "name": "taxonomy: NCBI TaxID", "value": "4932"}]}], "title": "Temporal profiling of redox-dependent heterogeneity in single cells"}